1. Definitions.

   "Project" means the RavenTag software, protocol specification (RTP-1),
   and documentation made available under this License, including all
   source code, binaries, configuration files, and associated materials
   published at: https://github.com/ALENOC/RavenTag

   "Derivative Project" means any work that is based on, derived from,
   incorporates, or modifies the Project in whole or in part, including
   forks, ports, adaptations, plugins, and software that embeds or wraps
   the Project, regardless of the programming language or platform used.

   "Blockchain Operations" means any interaction with a distributed ledger,
   including but not limited to: asset issuance, asset transfer, asset
   revocation or burn, on-chain metadata registration, and any read or
   write operation performed via RPC or API against a blockchain node.

   "Ravencoin Blockchain" means the Ravencoin mainnet and testnet as
   defined by the Ravencoin open-source project (https://ravencoin.org),
   identified by its genesis block hash. In the event of a chain split or
   fork of the Ravencoin network, "Ravencoin Blockchain" shall refer to
   the chain that retains the majority of the original development
   community and hashrate, as determined by the copyright holder.

   "Commercial Use" means any use of the Project or a Derivative Project
   that is intended for or results in commercial advantage or monetary
   compensation, including but not limited to: selling products or services
   that incorporate the Project, offering the Project as a hosted or managed
   service, or using the Project to generate revenue directly or indirectly.

   "Distribute" means to make the Project or a Derivative Project available to
   any third party, whether by sale, transfer, hosting, or any other means,
   in source or binary form.

   "You" (or "Your") means the individual or legal entity exercising the
   rights granted by this License.

   "Copyright Holder" means Alessandro Nocentini, the original author
   and sole copyright holder of the Project.

