3. Conditions.

   Any use, reproduction, or distribution of the Project or a Derivative
   Project, in source or binary form, requires full compliance with all of
   the following conditions:

   (a) Attribution. You must:

         i.  Retain, in all copies and Derivative Projects, the original
             copyright notice: "Copyright 2026-present Alessandro Nocentini".

         ii. Include a clearly visible statement that the work is derived
             from RavenTag, with a link to:
               https://github.com/ALENOC/RavenTag

         iii. Display the RavenTag name and logo in any public-facing
              documentation, README, application About screen, or
              equivalent user-visible location of the Derivative Project.

         iv. Not remove, obscure, or alter any copyright, trademark, or
             attribution notices contained in the Project.

   (b) Ravencoin Requirement. Any use or Derivative Project that performs
       Blockchain Operations must use the Ravencoin Blockchain exclusively
       for all such operations.

       The following are explicitly and unconditionally prohibited:

         i.  Replacing or substituting the Ravencoin Blockchain with any
             other blockchain, distributed ledger, token protocol, or
             smart contract platform, including but not limited to
             Ethereum, Solana, Polygon, Bitcoin, Cardano, Tezos, or any
             EVM-compatible or non-EVM chain.

         ii. Abstracting, wrapping, or configuring the blockchain layer
             in a way that permits runtime or compile-time selection of
             any blockchain other than Ravencoin.

         iii. Distributing or deploying any version of the Project, modified
              or unmodified, that is configured, documented, or intended
              to operate on a blockchain other than Ravencoin.

         iv. Removing, bypassing, or replacing the Ravencoin RPC client
             or any component whose primary function is interaction with
             the Ravencoin Blockchain.

   (c) Share Alike. Any Derivative Project that is publicly Distributed or
       deployed to third parties must be released exclusively under this
       same License (RTSL-1.0). You may not impose additional restrictions
       on the rights granted by this License, nor may You apply a more
       permissive license to a Derivative Project.

   (d) Notice of Changes. Any file that You modify must carry a prominent
       notice at the top of the file stating: (1) that You changed the
       file, and (2) the date of the change.

   (e) No Misrepresentation. You must not misrepresent the origin of the
       Project. You must not claim that You are the original author of the
       Project or any substantial portion of it. You must not use the name
       "RavenTag" or the name "Alessandro Nocentini" to endorse or promote
       Derivative Projects without prior written permission.

   (f) Protocol Compatibility. Any Derivative Project that programs NFC
       chips, issues Ravencoin assets, or performs tag verification must
       maintain full compatibility with the RTP-1 protocol specification
       as defined in the Project documentation (docs/protocol.md). Specifically:

         i.  NFC chips programmed by a Derivative Project must remain
             verifiable by the unmodified RavenTag Verify application
             without requiring any changes to the app.

         ii. The SUN (Secure Unique NFC) verification URL structure,
             query parameter names (e, m, asset), and CMAC computation
             method must not be altered in a way that breaks compatibility
             with the native verification flow.

         iii. The Ravencoin asset naming hierarchy (root / sub-asset /
              unique token) and the nfc_pub_id derivation method
              (SHA-256(uid || BRAND_SALT)) must not be changed in any
              manner incompatible with the RTP-1 specification.

         iv. You may extend the protocol with additional optional
             parameters or features, provided that such extensions are
             strictly additive and do not break the baseline RTP-1
             verification flow for any compliant verifier.

       The intent of this clause is to ensure that any physical product
       tagged using a Derivative Project can always be verified by any
       RTP-1 compliant application, including the native RavenTag Verify
       app, without requiring the end user to install a proprietary or
       modified verifier. Modifications that would lock end users into a
       single Derivative Project's verification app are prohibited.

