5. Blockchain and Wallet Disclaimer.

   (a) Blockchain Risk. The Ravencoin Blockchain is a decentralized,
       open-source network operated by independent third parties over
       which the Copyright Holder has no control. The Copyright Holder
       makes no warranty and assumes no liability for:

         i.  The availability, continuity, stability, or security of the
             Ravencoin Blockchain or any Ravencoin network node.

         ii. Any loss of assets, tokens, or data resulting from blockchain
             congestion, forks, protocol changes, node failures, or any
             other event affecting the Ravencoin network.

         iii. The accuracy, finality, or immutability of any transaction
              broadcast to the Ravencoin Blockchain using this Project.

         iv. Any regulatory action, legal restriction, or government
             intervention affecting the Ravencoin Blockchain or the
             use of Ravencoin assets in any jurisdiction.

         v.  The market value, liquidity, or exchangeability of Ravencoin
             (RVN) or any asset issued on the Ravencoin Blockchain.

   (b) Wallet and Key Management Risk. This Project includes functionality
       for generating, storing, and managing cryptographic keys and
       BIP39/BIP44 HD wallets. You acknowledge and accept that:

         i.  You are solely responsible for the secure backup, storage,
             and protection of all mnemonic phrases, private keys, and
             cryptographic secrets generated or managed by this Project.

         ii. Loss of a mnemonic phrase or private key results in
             permanent and irrecoverable loss of access to any associated
             Ravencoin assets. The Copyright Holder cannot recover lost
             keys or assets under any circumstances.

         iii. The Copyright Holder is not liable for any loss of funds,
              assets, or data resulting from key mismanagement, device
              failure, malware, unauthorized access, or any other cause.

         iv. This Project is not a custodial service. The Copyright Holder
             does not hold, store, or have access to Your private keys
             or funds at any time.

         v.  You are responsible for verifying the correctness of any
             transaction before broadcasting it to the Ravencoin Blockchain.
             Blockchain transactions are irreversible once confirmed.

   (c) NFC Hardware Risk. The Copyright Holder makes no warranty regarding
       the security, compatibility, or longevity of any NFC hardware,
       including NTAG 424 DNA chips or any other NFC tag used in
       conjunction with this Project. The Copyright Holder is not liable
       for any failure, cloning attempt, or physical damage affecting
       NFC hardware.

   (e) Consumer and Financial Risk. This Project is not a financial service,
